			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My question is why are not these classes closer when it comes to spell damage/mana ratio/speed? 
<br />

<br />
We always use the answer "we have our pet" but the wizard has so much other stuff in their bag and we fail to count it as a plus over us and pets.
<br />
They carry most of the same spells we have like shields/eye/resist buffs etc and have many more that we do not have.
<br />

<br />
1. Absorb Damage:  They say we have pet for this, but our pet is a big IF. If we have one up, If he can get the argo to help us, if the damage we are taking is not spell damage.  I really do not compare the two as being the same. 
<br />

<br />
2. Evac, TL:  Two major spells that equal mage utility spells, so neither of us have advantage in utility.
<br />

<br />
3. Root/snare: Major advantage to wizards. no matter what your arugement about "earth pets have root" wizards have a hugh advantage in this area.
<br />

<br />
4. Sow/buffs: wizards have another hugh advantage here with having the same buff as a mage and also their own personal resist buff along with familiar buffs that put the wizard well ahead of the mage in hp/resist/mana buffs
<br />

<br />
5. Stun/better hitting spells/better speed:  wizards once again are well ahead of mages in this area. We get zero stuns in our spells and saying air pet is as good once again is wrong for the limitations pets have. The other part is that mages find themselves in battle with nothing in their bag of spells that will hit gives the wizard major advantage once again.
<br />
At least make mage spells as fast as wizards. They shouldn't have that kind of advantage over us. 
<br />

<br />
6. Better crits/damage modifiers:  With their higher crit abilities and 30% spell damage modifier buff puts them once again leaps and bounds above the mage.  To even say we have a bracer is so wrong for they can get a bracer every day and it last all day makes our bracer really not a player. Also are summon stuff slowly becomes replaced with real equipment with same or better modifiers.
<br />

<br />
7. Spell argo reducer:  Hugh advantage to the wizards here, and at the higher level of play this alone out weighs the fact we have a pet at all.
<br />

<br />
Looking at all this I can't say having a pet equals us out.  
<br />

<br />
1. Mages can keep DD limitations but need equal damage/mana ratio on spell and same crit abilities. If a mage top DDs hit like wizard's top DDs but were limited to fire and magic it would be enough limitation. Having a lure type spell, but takes more mana than the wizards would not be over powering too.  Druids are equal to mages in nuking and they bring alot of other stuff to the table, so here is a example of a class that doesn't take a hit in there DPS ability because of their other abilities.  Where the mage gets hit hard just because of his pet even with all the other limitations our class has.
<br />
 
<br />
2. Mages need spell argo reducer (in a bad way) This alone puts wizard DPS leaps and bounds over anything a mage can do.
<br />

<br />
3. Mages having damage absortion is not out of line. Hell, we are like the only caster class with no speed modifier or FD ability. We actually need it more than the other classes that have it.
<br />

<br />
4. We do not heal or buff/debuff but in limited ways. We are like wizards in that we bring damage to the table, we should be close to equal in this area and our utilities sets us a part.  
<br />

<br />
The bottom line is the mage class is the most limited caster class out there. We take big hits just because we have a pet while lacking many basic spells that all the other caster classes have.  There is a reason a guild will have like 2 to 5 mages and unlimited wizards, and a guild finds it's self limited when they happen to have a good mage population but are lacking in wizards.  Many other classes will over lap in areas that a guild needs and the mage and wizard needs to over lap in the area of spell damage.  If you could say 7 or 8 mages would equal 5 wizards in all spell damage situation this would alow guilds to work with either class and off set the damage that pets may do.  As it is now the is no equality in the two classes.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
