			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Since it is so hard to compare different utilities, as a <span style="text-decoration: underline">first</span> approximation I would assume mage pet and so on, <span style="text-decoration: underline">roughly</span> balances wizard utility.  I find mages tend to undervalue pets, whereas wizards tend to undervalue root, snare, stun, and so on.
<br />

<br />
With that as a starting point, I would then argue that since mages are supposed to be <span style="font-style: italic">"respected damage dealers"</span>, we should do comparable damage to wizards on raids.
<br />

<br />
This allows us to look at damage, which, unlike utility, is easy to compare.
<br />

<br />
By avoiding comparisons of utility, we make the analysis easier and more comprehensible.
<br />

<br />
As <span style="font-style: italic">"respected damage dealers,"</span> mages should be sought after in raids, and are not.  That needs remedying.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Razamatazz Pizzazz</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
