			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Mages and wizards should be similiar for we fill the same rolls.
<br />

<br />
 In a fight we both do damage 99% of the time. Wizard with spells and mage with spells, pet, and DS, But the big problem is the mage carries hugh disavantages with his spells damage and pet and the wizard carries hugh advantages with his spell only attack. 
<br />

<br />
As was stated why does the mage have so many limitations on his spells?
<br />
Damage/mana ratio, casting time, argo, resists and the wizard beats the mage in all these areas plus has many ways to augment their spells even more.  I can see this for druids/shammy who have more than one major roll, but mages and wizards have only one major roll and it is the same and they only differ in minor utility rolls.  
<br />

<br />
If the mage damage spell were as versatle as the wizards, but wizards had a little better damage/ratio and mana pool to compensate for mage pets then we would be on the right track, and the question of a guild picking a mage or wizard for damage would be a mute point.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
