			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If a guild is looking for a damage dealer, mage, wizard, rogue, ranger, they'll take what they can get. If a guild is looking for a unique role to fill (spell based damage), they're going to take a wizard, short and simple. Magicians are a substitute high damage nuker with a melee backup.
<br />

<br />
Where the problem really lies is in the distinct <span style="font-style: italic">lack</span> of unique abilities between classes, notably magician and wizard. Wizards get a lot more abilities (Teleports being a good one) than magicians do. Amung utility, though, not many wizards are using them on raids, except for AE TL, similar to our AE Rods. They don't root, snare on raids, though regularly they are asked to spellshield. Beyond that, their utility doesn't come into play regularly on any raid I've been with on my guild, no more so than our meager utility does. I do think a diverging of abilities is probably good, however, with magicians, wizards, etc getting unique abilities amungst them.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
