				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree to a point. We do get unque abilities but they tend to lead to 2 boxing one mage to do those abilities.  When you look at the major rolls there are 5. The rest of all the classes abilities are utilities. Some are great and some suck, but unless they fit here are still just utilities. 
<br />

<br />
1. Tank/argo  2. Damage 3. Heal  4. buff/debuff  5. crowed control/pulling
<br />

<br />
Looking at anyone class you will find if they are top in one area they lack a lot in others. (we not talking about warrior argo problems hehe). And a class can have close to the best in multi areas, but not be top in any.
<br />

<br />
Looking at the druild they have great damage and great heals and good buff, but are not top in any area. Over all they can fill different rolls.  Enc have top buff and top crowed control but are very low in other areas. 
<br />

<br />
BLs have good tankage, good buffs, and good DPS once again not top but fill in needed splaces that other can't as well.
<br />

<br />
Wizard top damage in spell and most likely all around, but have nothing else in the major rolls
<br />

<br />
Mage good damage in spells/pet, but limited and have nothing else in the major rolls.
<br />

<br />
This is what makes the mage a low in demand class for a guild.  A guild on the upper end of ther server normally want limited slots per class. The usefulness of those classes are what sets their limit. When you see 3 mages in a guild and 15 wizards with the recruit page list needed mages as 0 and wizards as unlimited there is something about the mage class that is lacking to them.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
